or endpoint, sampling strategy (with options like AlwaysOn or TraceIdRatioBased), service name, and queue/batch parameters. I'm still verifying the exact key names against the documentation.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the actual implementation: I need to create an ingress routing `otel.example.com` to the healthy `demo-app` service, then patch the ingress-nginx ConfigMap to enable OpenTelemetry with the appropriate settings and a custom log format that includes the trace and span IDs. The key variables in the log format should be `$opentelemetry_trace_id` and `$opentelemetry_span_id`. I need to format the log entry as a single line in the ConfigMap, combining the trace ID and span ID fields with the rest of the upstream log format.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":813,"cache_read_input_tokens":32192,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":813},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2db1e2f7-a0ab-40dd-9104-9d898d6c4257","uuid":"5f335d1b-a219-4148-897d-b33be01fadcb","request_id":"req_011Cc6cJGxDyM2i1vzrQggHU"}
